<p>I would like to create some radio buttons inside labels. The Rails way of writing it which i know is by using radio_button_tag and label_tag.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;%= radio_button_tag 'tone', tone, false, id: "tone-#{tone}" %&gt; &lt;%= label_tag "tone-#{tone}", jp_name %&gt; </code></pre>  <p>which will generate these:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="radio" name="tone" id="tone-red" value="red"&gt; &lt;label for="tone-red"&gt;赤&lt;/label&gt; &lt;input type="radio" name="tone" id="tone-blue" value="blue"&gt; &lt;label for="tone-blue"&gt;青&lt;/label&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But due to the spaces between the text and the radio button, the in between spaces was unclickable. I would like to fix it by wrapping the radio buttons inside the label.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;label for="tone-red"&gt;赤   &lt;input type="radio" name="tone" id="tone-red" value="red"&gt; &lt;/label&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to generate these kind of html with Rails style?</p>  <p>JSFiddle: <a href="https://jsfiddle.net/21d34zqt/" rel="nofollow">https://jsfiddle.net/21d34zqt/</a></p>